urgical Facility. Additionally, Pennsylvania is one of the states where Halloween Adventure Stores has locations and where Sidney J. Blatt was born. The state has designated the Great Dane as its official state dog breed.\n\nGeographically, Pennsylvania encompasses a diverse landscape, including the Clinton Group and its equivalents. The state is partially covered by NJN's television network and includes the Dover Area School District. Historically, Pennsylvania was home to various flora, including Solidago Curtisii, while Solidago rupestris, once found in the region, is now extirpated. The state is also the setting for the fictional town of Pine Valley and the location where Luke Robert Laird was born in Hartstown. Additionally, Pennsylvania was the site of a failed proposal for ag-gag laws. The Genesee River also flows through the state, and Venango County is located within its borders. Easton is known for imposing no cigar tax.\n\nPennsylvania is also home to various other locations, including Exton, the Whitford Lodge, Huntingdon Valley, Chester, and the former base of Paragon Software. Additionally, TD Bank offers its services in the state. Pittsburgh, located in Pennsylvania, is the home of the Pittsburgh Steelers. Philadelphia, another major city in the state, is known for its historical and cultural significance.<SEP>Pennsylvania is a state in the United States where Hershey is located.<SEP>Pennsylvania is a state in the United States where Harsco Corporation is headquartered.<SEP>Pennsylvania is a state in the United States where Erie is located.<SEP>Pennsylvania is a state in the United States, with the 10th Congressional District located in its central and northeast regions.<SEP>Pennsylvania is a state in the United States where the town of Gettysburg is located.<SEP>Pennsylvania is a state in the United States where Joseph Grayson \"Joe\" Long was born."}
