{"entity": "Seattle", "type": "location", "description": "Seattle is a city located in the state of Washington, United States, renowned for its vibrant cultural and athletic contributions. The city boasts a rich musical heritage, particularly in the grunge music movement, and is the birthplace of several influential bands and musicians, including Mad Season, Skin Yard, Bam Bam, Gruntruck, and Foo Fighters. Additionally, Seattle is home to Jack Endino's Soundhouse Recording, further cementing its significance in the music industry. The rock group Cat Butt was also formed in Seattle, adding to its diverse musical landscape. Notable bands such as Sunny Day Real Estate and The Fire Theft also originated in Seattle, highlighting its continued influence in the music scene.\n\nIn the realm of sports, Seattle has a competitive presence in collegiate basketball, with a team that participated in the College Basketball Invitational, defeating the Vermont Catamounts and the Colorado Buffaloes men's basketball team. The city is also associated with Football Club Seattle Storm and is home to Seattle Sounders FC 2, underscoring its athletic prowess.\n\nSeattle's cultural landmarks include the Market Theater Gum Wall, the Langston Hughes Performing Arts Institute, and The 5th Avenue Theatre, each contributing to the city's unique identity. The city is also known for locations such as Hat 'n' Boots and was the operating base for G.O. Guy. Additionally, Seattle served as the starting location of the Glow in the Dark Tour on April 16, 2008. These elements collectively make Seattle a significant location in both entertainment and sports.\n\nSeattle is also home to several notable institutions and businesses. It is the base for the Discovery Institute and the record label and/OAR, underscoring its role as a hub for various intellectual and cultural endeavors. The city is one of the current locations of Patxi's pizzeria chain and is known for being the location of the Original Starbucks. Additionally, Seattle is the site of the 2nd & Pike skyscraper construction and the Butterworth Building. Jeff Sampson currently resides in Seattle, further adding to its diverse community.\n\nSeattle is also known for its historic Pike Place Market, which is a significant cultural and commercial landmark. The city is home to the Pike Place Fish Market and the Left Bank Books Collective, further enriching its cultural landscape. The Market Theater Gum Wall is another notable location within Seattle, contributing to its unique identity.\n\nBeyond its cultural and musical contributions, Seattle is the city where Early Winters, Ltd. was founded and where Something Weird Video is based. It is also the hometown of Randall Dunn and the birthplace of Davey Brozowski. Additionally, Seattle is the city in Washington where the band Loaded was formed and where Jesse Robinson was raised. These diverse connections underscore Seattle's role as a dynamic and influential urban center.<SEP>Seattle is a city in Washington state, near Issaquah.<SEP>Seattle is the city in Washington where the band Tall Birds originated.<SEP>Seattle is the market where Delilah Rene first aired as \"Delilah Rene\".<SEP>Seattle is a city in Washington where the Alaska Trade Building is located.<SEP>Seattle is the city where Heart's final concert of the Summer of Love Tour was held."}
